
[1]strop

   STROP, n.

   1. A strap. [See Strap.] This orthography is particularly used for a
   strip of lether used for sharpening razors and giving them a fine
   smooth edge; a razor-strop. But strap is preferable.

   2. A piece of rope spliced into a circular wreath, and put round a
   block for hanging it.
